/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
//                          -- ABOUT --
//
// BasealtTask utility (x86-64 Linux) performs next functions: 
// 
// 1. The utility gets lists of binary packages from two branches of ALT repository
// 
// 2. The utility makes a comparision of received lists and makes json output to stream (console output default)
// 
// 3. Final json displays:
// - all packages that are in the 1st but not in the 2nd (OuterLeft title)
// - all packages that are in the 2nd but not in the 1st (OuterRight title)
// - all packages whose version-release is greater in the 1st than in the 2nd
//
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// 
//                      -- BUILD REQUIREMENTS --
//
// 1. CMake 3.22
// 
// 2. CURL 4.X (libcurl-devel)
// 
// 3. Nlohmann-json (nlohmann-json-devel)
//
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
//                          -- INSTALL --
//
// 1. Open 'Basealt' folder in terminal.
//
// 2. Type 'bash ./install.sh'.
//
// 3. Done. Type 'basealttask' and use utility.
//
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////